description*.en: The incidence rate is a measure of the frequency with which a disease or other incident occurs over a specified time period. It is also known as the incidence density rate or person-time incidence rate, when the denominator is the combined person-time of the population at risk (the sum of the time duration of exposure across all persons exposed)

title: IncidenceRate
description: The incidence rate is a measure of the frequency with which a disease or other incident occurs over a specified time period. It is also known as the incidence density rate or person-time incidence rate, when the denominator is the combined person-time of the population at risk (the sum of the time duration of exposure across all persons exposed)
